voting stations this weekend, over 1.4 million used the opportunity to
re-register in their current voting district and 885 758 used the opportunity
to change their registration to a new voting district," the IEC said in a
statement. However, 490
520 were voters registered to vote for the first time.It's reported that the Gauteng province saw the
most new registration at 23.69% followed by KwaZulu-Natal with 18.78% and the
Limpopo with 17.03%.The IEC confirmed that the voters’ roll now stands
at 26 250 939 voters which is estimated to be approximately 75% of the eligible
voting population based on Statistics South Africa voting age population
estimates.